objecttypes.name: AbstractMaster
objecttypes.description: Properties shared with all master-data schema instances.

properties.name: NameAliases
properties.description: Alternative names, including historical, by which this master data is/has been known (it should include all the identifiers).

properties.name: GeoContexts
properties.description: List of geographic entities which provide context to the master data. This may include multiple types or multiple values of the same type.

properties.name: SpatialLocation
properties.description: The spatial location information such as coordinates, CRS information (left empty when not appropriate).

properties.name: VersionCreationReason
properties.description: This describes the reason that caused the creation of a new version of this master data.

objecttypes.name: AbstractActivityParameter
objecttypes.description:
General parameter value used in one instance of activity.
[Without inheritance, combined specializations.]

properties.name: Title
properties.description: Name of the parameter, used to identify it in the activity. It must have an equivalent in the ActivityTemplate parameters.

properties.name: Index
properties.description: When parameter is an array, used to indicate the index in the array.

properties.name: Selection
properties.description: Textual description about how this parameter was selected.

properties.name: Keys
properties.description: A nested array describing keys used to identify a parameter value. When multiple values are provided for a given parameter, the key provides a way to identify the parameter through its association with an object, a time index or a parameter array member via ParameterKey value.

properties.name: DataObjectParameter
properties.description: Parameter referencing to a top level object.

properties.name: DataQuantityParameter
properties.description: Parameter containing a double value.

properties.name: IntegerQuantityParameter
properties.description: Parameter containing an integer value.

properties.name: StringParameter
properties.description: Parameter containing a string value.

properties.name: TimeIndexParameter
properties.description: Parameter containing a time index value.  It is assumed that all TimeIndexParameters within an Activity have the same date-time format, which is then described by the FrameOfReference mechanism.

properties.name: ParameterKindID
properties.description: [Added to cover lack of inheritance]

properties.name: ParameterRoleID
properties.description: Reference data describing how the parameter was used by the activity, such as input, output, control, constraint, agent, predecessor activity, successor activity.

properties.name: DataQuantityParameterUOMID
properties.description: Identifies unit of measure for floating point value.

objecttypes.name: AbstractSpatialLocation
objecttypes.description: A geographic object which can be described by a set of points.

properties.name: SpatialLocationCoordinatesDate
properties.description: Date when coordinates were measured or retrieved.

properties.name: QuantitativeAccuracyBandID
properties.description: An approximate quantitative assessment of the quality of a location (accurate to > 500 m (i.e. not very accurate)), to < 1 m, etc.

properties.name: QualitativeSpatialAccuracyTypeID
properties.description: A qualitative description of the quality of a spatial location, e.g. unverifiable, not verified, basic validation.

properties.name: CoordinateQualityCheckPerformedBy
properties.description: The user who performed the Quality Check.

properties.name: CoordinateQualityCheckDateTime
properties.description: The date of the Quality Check.

properties.name: CoordinateQualityCheckRemarks
properties.description: Freetext remarks on Quality Check.

properties.name: AsIngestedCoordinates
properties.description: The original or 'as ingested' coordinates (Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon or MultiPolygon). The name 'AsIngestedCoordinates' was chosen to contrast it to 'OriginalCoordinates', which carries the uncertainty whether any coordinate operations took place before ingestion. In cases where the original CRS is different from the as-ingested CRS, the OperationsApplied can also contain the list of operations applied to the coordinate prior to ingestion. The data structure is similar to GeoJSON FeatureCollection, however in a CRS context explicitly defined within the AbstractAnyCrsFeatureCollection. The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. 'eastward/longitude', 'northward/latitude' {, 'upward/height' unless overridden by an explicit direction in the AsIngestedCoordinates.VerticalCoordinateReferenceSystemID}.

properties.name: Wgs84Coordinates
properties.description: The normalized coordinates (Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon or MultiPolygon) based on WGS 84 (EPSG:4326 for 2-dimensional coordinates, EPSG:4326 + EPSG:5714 (MSL) for 3-dimensional coordinates). This derived coordinate representation is intended for global discoverability only. The schema of this substructure is identical to the GeoJSON FeatureCollection https://geojson.org/schema/FeatureCollection.json. The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. longitude, latitude {, height}

properties.name: AppliedOperations
properties.description: The audit trail of operations applied to the coordinates from the original state to the current state. The list may contain operations applied prior to ingestion as well as the operations applied to produce the Wgs84Coordinates. The text elements refer to ESRI style CRS and Transformation names, which may have to be translated to EPSG standard names.

properties.name: SpatialParameterTypeID
properties.description: A type of spatial representation of an object, often general (e.g. an Outline, which could be applied to Field, Reservoir, Facility, etc.) or sometimes specific (e.g. Onshore Outline, State Offshore Outline, Federal Offshore Outline, 3 spatial representations that may be used by Countries).

properties.name: SpatialGeometryTypeID
properties.description: Indicates the expected look of the SpatialParameterType, e.g. Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon, MultiPolygon. The value constrains the type of geometries in the GeoJSON Wgs84Coordinates and AsIngestedCoordinates.

objecttypes.name: AbstractWPCActivity
objecttypes.description: The activity abstraction included by projects (master-data) and work-product-component group-type specialisations.

properties.name: ActivityTemplateID
properties.description: The relation to the ActivityTemplate carrying expected parameter definitions and default values.

properties.name: ParentProjectID
properties.description: The relationship to a parent project acting as a parent activity.

properties.name: ParentActivityID
properties.description: The relationship to a parent activity.

properties.name: Parameters
properties.description: General parameter value used in one instance of activity.  Includes reference to data objects which are inputs and outputs of the activity.

properties.name: PriorActivityIDs
properties.description: The activity or activities feeding results into this activity instance.

properties.name: SoftwareSpecifications
properties.description: Software names and versions used.

objecttypes.name: AbstractWPCGroupType
objecttypes.description: Generic reference object containing the universal group-type properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

properties.name: Artefacts
properties.description: An array of Artefacts - each artefact has a Role, Resource tuple. An artefact is distinct from the file, in the sense certain valuable information is generated during loading process (Artefact generation process). Examples include retrieving location data, performing an OCR which may result in the generation of artefacts which need to be preserved distinctly

properties.name: IsExtendedLoad
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is undergoing an extended load.  It reflects the fact that the work product component is in an early stage and may be updated before finalization.

properties.name: IsDiscoverable
properties.description: A flag that indicates if the work product component is searchable, which means covered in the search index.

objecttypes.name: AbstractWorkProductComponent
objecttypes.description: Generic reference object containing the universal properties of a Work Product Component for inclusion in data type specific Work Product Component objects

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Name

properties.name: Description
properties.description: Description.  Summary of the work product component.  Not the same as Remark which captures thoughts of creator about the wpc.

properties.name: CreationDateTime
properties.description: Date that a resource (work  product component here) is formed outside of OSDU before loading (e.g. publication date).

properties.name: Tags
properties.description: Array of key words to identify the work product, especially to help in search.

properties.name: SpatialPoint
properties.description: A centroid point that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: SpatialArea
properties.description: A polygon boundary that reflects the locale of the content of the work product component (location of the subject matter).

properties.name: GeoContexts
properties.description: List of geographic entities which provide context to the WPC.  This may include multiple types or multiple values of the same type.

properties.name: SubmitterName
properties.description: Name of the person that first submitted the work product component to OSDU.

properties.name: BusinessActivities
properties.description: Array of business processes/workflows that the work product component has been through (ex. well planning, exploration).

properties.name: AuthorIDs
properties.description: Array of Authors' names of the work product component.  Could be a person or company entity.

properties.name: LineageAssertions
properties.description: Defines relationships with other objects (any kind of Resource) upon which this work product component depends.  The assertion is directed only from the asserting WPC to ancestor objects, not children.  It should not be used to refer to files or artefacts within the WPC -- the association within the WPC is sufficient and Artefacts are actually children of the main WPC file. They should be recorded in the Data.Artefacts[] array.

properties.name: RoleID
properties.description: The SRN of this artefact's role.

properties.name: ResourceKind
properties.description: The kind or schema ID of the artefact. Resolvable with the Schema Service.

properties.name: ResourceID
properties.description: The SRN which identifies this OSDU Artefact resource.

objecttypes.name: DatasetsItems
objecttypes.description: The SRN which identifies this OSDU File resource.

objecttypes.name: KeysItems
objecttypes.description:
Abstract class describing a key used to identify a parameter value. When multiple values are provided for a given parameter, provides a way to identify the parameter through its association with an object, a time index... 
[Without inheritance, combined specializations.]

properties.name: ObjectParameterKey
properties.description: Relationship to an object ID, which acts as the parameter.

properties.name: ParameterKey
properties.description: The key name, which establishes an association between parameters.

properties.name: ID
properties.description: The object reference identifying the DIRECT, INDIRECT, REFERENCE dependency.

properties.name: LineageRelationshipType
properties.description: Used by LineageAssertion to describe the nature of the line of descent of a work product component from a prior Resource, such as DIRECT, INDIRECT, REFERENCE.  It is not for proximity (number of nodes away), it is not to cover all the relationships in a full ontology or graph, and it is not to describe the type of activity that created the asserting WPC.  LineageAssertion does not encompass a full provenance, process history, or activity model.

objecttypes.name: SoftwareSpecificationsItems
objecttypes.description: The name and version of the software being executed in the context of this activity

properties.name: SoftwareName
properties.description: The name of the software, application or plug-in used while performing this activity.

properties.name: Version
properties.description: The version of the software, application or plug-in used while performing this activity.

objecttypes.name: AbstractGeoContext
objecttypes.description: A geographic context to an entity. It can be either a reference to a GeoPoliticalEntity, Basin, Field, Play or Prospect.

objecttypes.name: AbstractGeoFieldContext
objecttypes.description: A single, typed field entity reference, which is 'abstracted' to AbstractGeoContext and then aggregated by GeoContexts properties.

properties.name: GeoTypeID
properties.description: The fixed type 'Field' for this AbstractGeoFieldContext.

objecttypes.name: AbstractGeoPlayContext
objecttypes.description: A single, typed Play entity reference, which is 'abstracted' to AbstractGeoContext and then aggregated by GeoContexts properties.

properties.name: PlayID
properties.description: Reference to the play.

properties.name: GeoTypeID
properties.description: The PlayType reference of the Play (via PlayID) for application convenience.

objecttypes.name: AbstractGeoPoliticalContext
objecttypes.description: A single, typed geo-political entity reference, which is 'abstracted' to AbstractGeoContext and then aggregated by GeoContexts properties.

properties.name: GeoPoliticalEntityID
properties.description: Reference to GeoPoliticalEntity.

properties.name: GeoTypeID
properties.description: The GeoPoliticalEntityType reference of the GeoPoliticalEntity (via GeoPoliticalEntityID) for application convenience.

objecttypes.name: AbstractGeoProspectContext
objecttypes.description: A single, typed Prospect entity reference, which is 'abstracted' to AbstractGeoContext and then aggregated by GeoContexts properties.

properties.name: ProspectID
properties.description: Reference to the prospect.

properties.name: GeoTypeID
properties.description: The ProspectType reference of the Prospect (via ProspectID) for application convenience.

objecttypes.name: Field
objecttypes.description: A mineral deposit that has been exploited for commercial purposes.

properties.name: AsIngestedCoordinates
properties.description: The original or 'as ingested' coordinates (Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon or MultiPolygon). The name 'AsIngestedCoordinates' was chosen to contrast it to 'OriginalCoordinates', which carries the uncertainty whether any coordinate operations took place before ingestion. In cases where the original CRS is different from the as-ingested CRS, the OperationsApplied can also contain the list of operations applied to the coordinate prior to ingestion. The data structure is similar to GeoJSON FeatureCollection, however in a CRS context explicitly defined within the AbstractAnyCrsFeatureCollection. The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. 'eastward/longitude', 'northward/latitude' {, 'upward/height' unless overridden by an explicit direction in the AsIngestedCoordinates.VerticalCoordinateReferenceSystemID}.

properties.name: Wgs84Coordinates
properties.description: The normalized coordinates (Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon or MultiPolygon) based on WGS 84 (EPSG:4326 for 2-dimensional coordinates, EPSG:4326 + EPSG:5714 (MSL) for 3-dimensional coordinates). This derived coordinate representation is intended for global discoverability only. The schema of this substructure is identical to the GeoJSON FeatureCollection https://geojson.org/schema/FeatureCollection.json. The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. longitude, latitude {, height}

properties.name: AppliedOperations
properties.description: The audit trail of operations applied to the coordinates from the original state to the current state. The list may contain operations applied prior to ingestion as well as the operations applied to produce the Wgs84Coordinates. The text elements refer to ESRI style CRS and Transformation names, which may have to be translated to EPSG standard names.

properties.name: SpatialParameterTypeID
properties.description: A type of spatial representation of an object, often general (e.g. an Outline, which could be applied to Field, Reservoir, Facility, etc.) or sometimes specific (e.g. Onshore Outline, State Offshore Outline, Federal Offshore Outline, 3 spatial representations that may be used by Countries).

properties.name: SpatialGeometryTypeID
properties.description: Indicates the expected look of the SpatialParameterType, e.g. Point, MultiPoint, LineString, MultiLineString, Polygon, MultiPolygon. The value constrains the type of geometries in the GeoJSON Wgs84Coordinates and AsIngestedCoordinates.

The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. 'eastward/longitude', 'northward/latitude' {, 'upward/height' unless overridden by an explicit direction in the AsIngestedCoordinates.VerticalCoordinateReferenceSystemID}.

It should not be used to refer to files or artefacts within the WPC -- the association within the WPC is sufficient and Artefacts are actually children of the main WPC file. LineageAssertion does not encompass a full provenance, process history, or activity model.

objects.name: WellLog
objects.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

This derived coordinate representation is intended for global discoverability only. The schema of this substructure is identical to the GeoJSON FeatureCollection https://geojson.org/schema/FeatureCollection.json. The coordinate sequence follows GeoJSON standard, i.e. longitude, latitude {, height}
